<ac:structured-macro ac:name="panel" ac:schema-version="1" ac:macro-id="ce3b8454-fe5b-4ebf-bcb8-7cacf86de605"><ac:parameter ac:name="panelIcon">:warning:</ac:parameter><ac:parameter ac:name="panelIconId">atlassian-warning</ac:parameter><ac:parameter ac:name="bgColor">#FFF0B3</ac:parameter><ac:rich-text-body><p>This is a template, DO NOT directly edit and leave content here.</p><ol start="1"><li><p>To copy the template page and delete the guide lines.</p></li><li><p>Best practices <ac:link ac:card-appearance="inline"><ri:page ri:content-title="Engineering Best Practice &amp; Checklists" ri:version-at-save="28" /><ac:link-body>Engineering Best Practice &amp; Checklists</ac:link-body></ac:link> </p></li><li><p>Non-functional Requirements (NFRs) <ac:link ac:card-appearance="inline"><ri:page ri:content-title="Non-functional requirements (NFRs) [WIP]" ri:version-at-save="3" /><ac:link-body>Non-functional requirements (NFRs) [WIP]</ac:link-body></ac:link> </p></li></ol></ac:rich-text-body></ac:structured-macro><p /><ac:structured-macro ac:name="toc" ac:schema-version="1" data-layout="default" ac:local-id="27dcc1f8-7503-4bff-9aa5-c8edb24a50f7" ac:macro-id="d8d5ee186e3843de65e714598cb36f9c"><ac:parameter ac:name="minLevel">1</ac:parameter><ac:parameter ac:name="maxLevel">7</ac:parameter></ac:structured-macro><h1>Background</h1><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">High-level description on the requirement and objectives or facts/findings that related to this change. Includes business value and impact if possible.</span><span style="color: rgb(191,38,0);"> (Required) </span></p><h1>Objectives </h1><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">Clearly list the objectives and expected outcomes of the project to ensure alignment of expectations among the team and stakeholders. </span><span style="color: rgb(191,38,0);">(Required) </span></p><h1>Documents &amp; Versions</h1><h2>Specs</h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">Links of related information like BRD, PRD, Mockups, reference document, repo or even Slack conversation. </span><span style="color: rgb(191,38,0);">(Required)</span></p><table data-table-width="760" data-layout="default" ac:local-id="024eae5e-1712-4587-b769-f2b3835722c0"><colgroup><col style="width: 122.0px;" /><col style="width: 637.0px;" /></colgroup><tbody><tr><th><p><strong>BRD</strong></p></th><td><p /></td></tr><tr><th><p><strong>PRD</strong></p></th><td><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><th><p><strong>Mockups</strong></p></th><td><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><th><p><strong>Tickets</strong></p></th><td><p /></td></tr></tbody></table><h2>Versions </h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">Ensure document version numbers are consistent and clearly identified for tracking and differentiation. </span><span style="color: rgb(191,38,0);">(Required) </span></p><table data-table-width="760" data-layout="default" ac:local-id="12fcd7f9-2af4-4976-9027-12c79c895908"><colgroup><col style="width: 99.0px;" /><col style="width: 99.0px;" /><col style="width: 99.0px;" /><col style="width: 459.0px;" /></colgroup><tbody><tr><th><p><strong>Version</strong></p></th><th><p><strong>Date</strong></p></th><th><p><strong>Author</strong></p></th><th><p><strong>Remarks</strong></p></th></tr><tr><td><p /></td><td><p /></td><td><p /></td><td><p /></td></tr><tr><td><p /></td><td><p /></td><td><p /></td><td><p /></td></tr></tbody></table><h2>Terms &amp; Terminology</h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">Provide a glossary of technical terms and abbreviations used in the document.</span></p><h2>People</h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">List the project team members and their roles. </span><span style="color: rgb(191,38,0);">(Required) </span></p><table data-table-width="760" data-layout="default" ac:local-id="d11a5ffd-ce02-444c-bc67-57c1f4085236"><colgroup><col style="width: 160.0px;" /><col style="width: 599.0px;" /></colgroup><tbody><tr><th><p><strong>SA</strong></p></th><td><p /></td></tr><tr><th><p><strong>Designer</strong></p></th><td><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><th><p><strong>Tech Lead</strong></p></th><td><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><th><p><strong>QA/QE</strong></p></th><td><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><th><p><strong>Product</strong></p></th><td><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><th><p><strong>PMO</strong></p></th><td><p>&nbsp;</p></td></tr></tbody></table><h1>Scope</h1><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">List out limitations and things that are planned but not included in this plan (with follow up document). </span><span style="color: rgb(191,38,0);">(Required by phases) </span></p><h2>Features</h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">List major features or functionalities.</span></p><h2>Feature Limitations</h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">Specify limitations or constraints on features.</span></p><h2>Excluded Content</h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">Clearly state what is not included in the project.</span></p><h1>Technical Detail</h1><h2>Architecture</h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">Diagram of existing or proposed architecture, possibly visualize dependencies between infrastructure, services, database storage, components or features. List out items like new service, tech stack, database introduced, caches, message queue or any other relevant changes to the system that impact its overall structure and functionality. </span><span style="color: rgb(191,38,0);">(Required if any changes) </span></p><h2>Database</h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">List out new changes on database with fields, description, possible values and validations. For new collection, please including UML diagram possibly with relation on existing models.</span></p><ac:task-list>
<ac:task>
<ac:task-id>9</ac:task-id>
<ac:task-uuid>9</ac:task-uuid>
<ac:task-status>incomplete</ac:task-status>
<ac:task-body><span class="placeholder-inline-tasks">Update schema map <ac:link ac:card-appearance="inline"><ri:page ri:content-title="Database Schema Map (EC)" ri:version-at-save="11" /><ac:link-body>Database Schema Map (EC)</ac:link-body></ac:link> </span></ac:task-body>
</ac:task>
<ac:task>
<ac:task-id>10</ac:task-id>
<ac:task-uuid>10</ac:task-uuid>
<ac:task-status>incomplete</ac:task-status>
<ac:task-body><span class="placeholder-inline-tasks">Update Document of relative Domain Model (e.g. <ac:link ac:card-appearance="inline"><ri:page ri:content-title="User Documentations - Model" ri:version-at-save="15" /><ac:link-body>User Documentations - Model</ac:link-body></ac:link> )</span></ac:task-body>
</ac:task>
<ac:task>
<ac:task-id>11</ac:task-id>
<ac:task-uuid>11</ac:task-uuid>
<ac:task-status>incomplete</ac:task-status>
<ac:task-body><span class="placeholder-inline-tasks">Prevent adding default value to columns of an embedded document (<ac:link ac:anchor="Prevent-default-value-in-embedded-document-field-(slack)"><ri:page ri:content-title="Engineering Best Practice &amp; Checklists" ri:version-at-save="28" /><ac:link-body>reason</ac:link-body></ac:link>)</span></ac:task-body>
</ac:task>
<ac:task>
<ac:task-id>12</ac:task-id>
<ac:task-uuid>12</ac:task-uuid>
<ac:task-status>incomplete</ac:task-status>
<ac:task-body><span class="placeholder-inline-tasks">State if you will do a <strong>double write</strong> if your changes involve moving some data from one database to another (include but not limited to <strong>one field to another, one collection to another, one cluster to another or even mongodb to tidb</strong>). Please briefly describe your plan about what, how and where your data is gonna move to. This could help downstream users of your data (eg, <strong>Data team)</strong> to evaluate whether they will be involved in this project.<span style="color: rgb(191,38,0);"> (Required if any changes)</span></span></ac:task-body>
</ac:task>
<ac:task>
