<ac:task-body><span class="placeholder-inline-tasks">Confirm with DBA how the db existing indices will be created (auto or manual?) in the new cluster if you need to migrate the db from one place to another. ( eg altas to self host ). </span></ac:task-body>
</ac:task>
</ac:task-list><h2>Logical Data Flow</h2><h2>Components </h2><table data-table-width="1800" data-layout="align-start" ac:local-id="296b55e2-88ae-4d35-acb5-c1de8a828c7a"><tbody><tr><th><p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Item</strong></p></th><th><p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Detail</strong></p></th><th><p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Man/Day</strong></p></th></tr><tr><td><p><strong>SHOP</strong></p></td><td><p /></td><td><p /></td></tr><tr><td><p><code>ProductReviewsController</code>#product_avg_reviews</p></td><td><p>新增GET action，拿取商品的平均review星等</p><p>request payload:</p><ac:structured-macro ac:name="code" ac:schema-version="1" ac:macro-id="7397cff9-4fc7-4d14-89a1-26275e289e4f"><ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[{ product_ids:[] }]]></ac:plain-text-body></ac:structured-macro><p>response payload:</p><ac:structured-macro ac:name="code" ac:schema-version="1" ac:macro-id="37b649cd-8e37-4c85-91ec-f97a56146b18"><ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[{  
  product_avg_reviews: {
    #{product_id_1} : 4.5,
    #{product_id_2} : 4,
    #{product_id_3} : 4.8,
  },
}]]></ac:plain-text-body></ac:structured-macro></td><td><p /></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>SEARCH</strong></p></td><td><p /></td><td><p /></td></tr><tr><td><p><code>ProductReviewsController</code>#product_avg_reviews</p></td><td><p>新增GET action，拿取商品的平均review星等</p><p>request payload:</p><ac:structured-macro ac:name="code" ac:schema-version="1" ac:macro-id="7285a2c4-a67e-4739-a402-c35d842a4083"><ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[{ product_ids:[] }]]></ac:plain-text-body></ac:structured-macro><p>response payload:</p><ac:structured-macro ac:name="code" ac:schema-version="1" ac:macro-id="c10eeaa4-4b38-407c-bf6a-27b52d5c5a6a"><ac:plain-text-body><![CDATA[{  
  product_avg_reviews: {
    #{product_id_1} : 4.5,
    #{product_id_2} : 4,
    #{product_id_3} : 4.8,
  },
}]]></ac:plain-text-body></ac:structured-macro></td><td><p /></td></tr><tr><td><p /></td><td><p /></td><td><p /></td></tr></tbody></table><h2>Error Handling </h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">List out expected errors and corresponding plans (e.g. retry on failure, rate limit, circuit breaker) and baseline handling on expected issues.</span></p><h2>Limitation and Foreseeable Issues </h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">List out hard Limits and potential Issue in production/long run.</span></p><h2>Security Checking </h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">e.g., Insecure Direct Object Reference (</span><a href="https://portswigger.net/web-security/access-control/idor"><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">IDOR</span></a><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">), User Authentication, Encryption Algorithm, Sensitive PII/Token Leaking.</span><span style="color: rgb(191,38,0);"> (Required if any relative) </span></p><ac:structured-macro ac:name="note" ac:schema-version="1" ac:macro-id="86128d0f-5e86-4035-9c80-136495560f17"><ac:rich-text-body><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">IDOR: Ensure that your API effectively verifies the ownership of resources. For instance, it should prevent unauthorized access to orders by confirming that the requester is the same merchant who initially authorized the transaction, rather than allowing access simply by altering the API URL. This security measure can be implemented by cross-referencing the merchant ID from the session or token (and not from the URL or POST body, which can be easily modified) with the corresponding entry in the database table. For example, you could use a query like Order.where(:owner_id =&gt; session.merchant_id) to enforce this ownership check.</span></p></ac:rich-text-body></ac:structured-macro><h2>Timeline and Phasing</h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">Provide the project timeline and phase execution plan to ensure task and delivery date clarity. </span><span style="color: rgb(191,38,0);">(Required)</span><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);"> </span></p><h1>Test Plan</h1><h2>Affected Area</h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">List out possibly affected features/areas and edge cases that to be concerned.  </span><span style="color: rgb(191,38,0);">(Required) </span></p><h2>Smoke Test</h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">List out expected smoke tests to be added. </span><span style="color: rgb(191,38,0);">(Required) </span></p><h2>Integration Test</h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">State if integration with other team is needed and expected key dates. </span><span style="color: rgb(191,38,0);">(Required) </span></p><h2>Unit Test</h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">List the expected unit test cases. </span><span style="color: rgb(191,38,0);">(Required) </span></p><h1>Release Plan</h1><h2>Dependencies</h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">Detail the dependencies with other systems or components to track and manage these dependencies effectively.  e.g. Blocked by XXX feature rollout. </span></p><h2>Migration</h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">List out the migration steps and possibly with sample data or projected issues.</span></p><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">e.g. new Liquid function </span><a href="https://shopline-layout.readme.io/docs/%E6%9C%83%E5%93%A1%E6%8E%A8%E8%96%A6%E7%8D%8E%E8%B3%9E-member-referral-campaign" data-card-appearance="inline">https://shopline-layout.readme.io/docs/%E6%9C%83%E5%93%A1%E6%8E%A8%E8%96%A6%E7%8D%8E%E8%B3%9E-member-referral-campaign</a> <span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);"> </span><span style="color: rgb(191,38,0);">(Required) </span></p><h2>Deployment</h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">List out prerequisite resources or procedure of deployment. </span><span style="color: rgb(191,38,0);"> (Required if any dependency) </span></p><h2>Performance Testing</h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">List out plan on application and service load test, including tools, number of samples, expected capacity.</span></p><h2>Monitoring</h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">List out monitoring tools and expected metrics/alarms to be measured/set. It&rsquo;s used to be a grafana link.  </span><span style="color: rgb(191,38,0);">(Required) </span></p><h2>Rollback</h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">List out steps to rollback and potential steps we need to execute (say correcting data or extra configuration).</span></p><h1>Others</h1><h2>FAQ</h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">List out questions and follow up items before/during implementation meetings to avoid repetitive questions.</span></p><h2>Appendix</h2><p><span style="color: rgb(151,160,175);">Less important or related supplementary materials.</span></p><p />
